  "texts": [
    "Common functional groups are shared by different sets of pathogen-responsive genesThe large number of genes unique to each population does not preclude overlapping functional response.",
    "We compared functional similarity among our DEGs, either in response to pathogen challenge or between R/S phenotype, using gene ontology (GO) terms (Fig. 3A and B).",
    "There were more shared GO terms than individual genes (Treatment: Mean % unique = 22.6, SEM % unique = 3.2; Phenotype: Mean % unique = 22.8, SEM % unique = 4.1; Fig. 2C), suggesting many of the defense-related genes in each population belong to shared functional responses.",
    "Even the GO terms that were unique to each population often shared similarity, e.g., \"response to auxin\" and \"auxin homeostasis\".",
    "While we tried to reduce redundant GO terms by exploiting the parent-child structure of GO directed acyclic graphs, some partially overlapping terms remained."
  ],
